## 6. Summary Table of Key Factors  

| Factor                        | Description                                                                                  | Impact on Youth Support for Communism/Socialism                 |
|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|
| Historical Ignorance           | Lack of knowledge about communist atrocities and conflation with socialism/social democracy | Leads to romanticized or naive views of communism               |
| Economic Disillusionment       | High debt, job insecurity, and perceived inequality                                         | Drives desire for redistributive economic policies              |
| Political Rhetoric & Media     | Softened anti-communism, praise of socialism by politicians, and social justice narratives  | Normalizes leftist ideologies and critiques of capitalism       |
| Educational Institutions       | Left-leaning faculty and ideological monoculture                                           | Influences student political views toward socialism/communism  |
| Psychological/Social Dynamics  | Youth idealism, rebellion, and emotional vulnerability                                      | Increases openness to radical alternatives                      |

